title: Could be better
text: I love Spotify, I just wish that they would change some things about the app. Being allowed only 6 skips per hour, not being able to listen to choose the song you want to listen to, not being able to have a song on repeat, always having your playlists on shuffle, and not being able to go back to a song is absolutely ridiculous. I totally understand the ads portion of it, however, I don't understand why people must pay to listen to music. It's absolutely ridiculous. If they want money then paying to get rid of ads as well as a few other advantages should be the only way they gain revenue rather than charging people to pay $120 per year just so they can play a song on repeat. Again, the ads I understand, though they can get annoying. Spotify is not a horrible platform, it could just use some improvements.
